Figure 1 shows the immunodetection of collagen type II in human adipose stromal
cells from monolayer cultures. Phase contrast microscopy is used in the upper panel;
Immunofluorescence is used in the lower panel.

Figure 3 shows immunodetection of collagen type IT in human adipose stromal
cells from alginate cultures. Phase contrast microscopy is used in the upper panel;
Immunofluorescence is used in the lower panel.
